-- Goldman, Morgan Stanley seek Dominion deal: WSJ
-- 
-- Wed Jan 24, 2007 5:01am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/24/us-goldman-morganstanley-idUSN2434040720070124

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The investing arms of Goldman Sachs Group Inc. ( GS.N ) and Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) are working on a private-equity play for the oil-and-gas assets of utility company Dominion Resources Inc. ( D.N ), which could be worth up to $15 billion, The Wall Street Journal reported on Wednesday. 

 The deal involves other private-equity players including Madison Dearborn Partners, Warburg Pincus, First Reserve and Carlyle Group and its affiliate Riverstone Holdings, the Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter. A second group including Blackstone Group, Texas Pacific Group and Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. is exploring its own offer, the Journal reported. Dominion, Goldman Sachs and Morgan Stanley officials were not immediately available for comment.